    "narrative_summary": "The BRCA2 missense change I1275M (c.3825A>G) is a reported germline variant that has been catalogued in multiple BRCA variant repositories, as noted in a large Chinese hereditary breast and ovarian cancer cohort study that compiled data from databases such as BED, BIC, BMD, ClinVar, LOVD and ENIGMA [PMC6617753]. The study highlighted extensive ethnic\u2011specific differences in BRCA1/2 variant spectra but did not provide any clinical classification, functional assay results, segregation data, or computational predictions for this particular substitution; the variant is simply listed among the total BRCA2 alterations identified. Because no direct evidence of pathogenicity or benign impact is presented, the current literature does not allow a definitive interpretation of I1275M. In the absence of supporting clinical or functional data, the variant remains of uncertain significance pending further investigation.",
